During the Niiname-sai, an ancient Shinto ritual that says thanks for the crops of the previous year{{sfnm|1a1=Britannica Kokusai Dai-Hyakkajiten|1y=2014}} and prays for fruitfulness in the following year,{{sfnm|1a1=Britannica Kokusai Dai-Hyakkajiten|1y=2014}} the [[Emperor of Japan]] says thanks to the {{illm|gods of heaven and earth|ja|天津神・国津神}}.{{sfnm|1a1=Britannica Kokusai Dai-Hyakkajiten|1y=2014}} It is held in the [[Imperial Palace]],{{sfnm|1a1=Britannica Kokusai Dai-Hyakkajiten|1y=2014}} as well as [[Ise Shrine]]{{sfnm|1a1=Britannica Kokusai Dai-Hyakkajiten|1y=2014}} and [[Izumo Shrine]].{{sfnm|1a1=Britannica Kokusai Dai-Hyakkajiten|1y=2014}}

